---
/**
 * Bhutan Wildlife — image LEFT, content RIGHT.
 * Content has a Read More toggle: first 2 paragraphs visible, last 2 collapsed.
 */
---

<section id="bhutan-wildlife" class="bg-cream relative py-20 lg:py-24">
  <div class="container-edge mx-auto">
    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-12 gap-12 lg:gap-16 items-start">

      {/* Content LEFT — with top padding so it doesn't start at image-top */}
      <div class="lg:col-span-6 lg:pt-12 xl:pt-16">
        <p class="text-eyebrow text-brand-orange mb-5 reveal-fast">A National Treasure</p>
        <h2 class="font-display text-h1 leading-[1.02] text-ink mb-8 reveal">
          Bhutan wildlife.
        </h2>

        <div class="space-y-5 text-ink-soft text-base lg:text-lg leading-relaxed">
          <p class="reveal">
            With over 70% of its land covered in forest, Bhutan is one of the
            world's most densely forested countries — and one of the very few
            nations that is proudly carbon-negative. Environmental protection
            is not simply policy here; it is enshrined within Bhutan's
            Constitution, which mandates that at least 60% of the country must
            remain under forest cover for all time.
          </p>
          <p class="reveal">
            This deep commitment to conservation has created one of the most
            pristine ecosystems on Earth. From the snow leopard roaming the
            high Himalayas and the endangered black-necked cranes arriving each
            winter, to Bengal tigers thriving at extraordinary altitudes,
            Bhutan's wilderness remains remarkably untouched.
          </p>

          {/* Collapsed by default — revealed via Read more */}
          <div id="wildlife-more" class="hidden space-y-5">
            <p>
              Ancient forests, remote valleys and sacred mountains are also
              woven with stories and mythology. Among them is the legend of
              the Yeti — the elusive guardian of the high Himalayas, long
              believed to inhabit Bhutan's remote alpine regions and still
              deeply rooted in local folklore.
            </p>
            <p>
              It is this rare balance between nature, spirituality and
              preservation that sets luxury journeys through Bhutan apart —
              offering privileged access to a kingdom that protects its soul
              as carefully as it welcomes its guests.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        {/* Read more / less toggle */}
        <button
          id="wildlife-toggle"
          class="mt-6 inline-flex items-center gap-3 text-sm tracking-wider text-ink hover:text-brand-orange transition-colors duration-300 border-b border-ink/40 pb-1 hover:border-brand-orange"
        >
          <span class="wildlife-toggle-label">Read more</span>
          <svg width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="wildlife-toggle-icon transition-transform duration-500">
            <line x1="12" y1="5" x2="12" y2="19" />
            <polyline points="19 12 12 19 5 12" />
          </svg>
        </button>
      </div>

      {/* Image RIGHT */}
      <div class="lg:col-span-6 lg:order-2">
        <div class="relative w-full aspect-[3/4] overflow-hidden rounded-sm shadow-[0_30px_60px_-30px_rgba(19,27,112,0.4)] img-zoom lg:sticky lg:top-28">
          <img src="/images/wildlife.jpg" alt="Bhutan wildlife" class="w-full h-full object-cover" loading="lazy" />
        </div>
      </div>

    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<script>
  const toggle = document.getElementById("wildlife-toggle");
  const more = document.getElementById("wildlife-more");
  const label = toggle?.querySelector(".wildlife-toggle-label");
  const icon = toggle?.querySelector(".wildlife-toggle-icon");

  toggle?.addEventListener("click", () => {
    if (!more) return;
    const open = !more.classList.contains("hidden");
    if (open) {
      more.classList.add("hidden");
      if (label) label.textContent = "Read more";
      icon?.classList.remove("rotate-180");
    } else {
      more.classList.remove("hidden");
      if (label) label.textContent = "Read less";
      icon?.classList.add("rotate-180");
    }
  });
</script>
